# Exchange Platform — Project Conventions

Authoritative requirements live in `openspec/specs/<capability>/spec.md`. When in doubt, read the relevant spec before implementing.

## Monorepo layout

- `apps/web` — Next.js frontend
- `apps/api` — NestJS backend
- `packages/shared` — shared types, DTOs, enums, formatters, constants (import as `@exchange/shared`)

Use pnpm workspaces. Add cross-app contracts to `packages/shared`, not duplicated in apps.

## Money and precision

- API JSON: monetary values as `string`, never JS float
- Calculations: `decimal.js` via `@exchange/shared` helpers (`add`, `sub`, `mul`, `isGte`)
- DB: Prisma `Decimal` / `DECIMAL(36, 18)`
- Display: `formatPrice`, `formatQuantity`, `formatPercent`, `formatVolume` from `@exchange/shared`

## Design system

- Use semantic Tailwind classes: `text-price-up`, `text-price-down`, `text-bid`, `text-ask`
- Do not hardcode hex colors in components; tokens are in `apps/web/src/app/globals.css`
- Default convention: green-up / red-down (`COLOR_CONVENTION` in shared)

## OpenSpec

- New features: use `/opsx:propose` and sync specs on archive
- Do not contradict synced specs without a new OpenSpec change
